node.text: You may have already seen or heard about the 40 cows escaping from a slaughter house in Pico Rivera, but I am here to ask you to consider what this means. I’ve received hundreds and hundreds of comments and messages ever since I started being vocal about veganism of people saying that animals “don’t experience emotion” or that “they don’t know any better”. This an example of how wrong all those statements are. These animals are sentient and know exactly what is going on. They’re terrified of their fate, they know they don’t stand a chance - that’s why these cows took the opportunity they saw to leave. If you eat meat and animal products, live your life, but you can’t say that these animals don’t feel or that they don’t want to live freely. They want a chance at living a safe, free and happy life just like us. Just because we have different wants and needs, doesn’t mean they don’t deserve a shot at an actual life. I’m so thankful to @farmsanctuary @dianewarren @simonereyes for rescuing one of these beautiful babies and allowing them to live their life out in sanctuary. My heart breaks for the other 39 who did not get as lucky. I’ve wanted to post about this for days, but it made me sick to think about. Their bravery was so beautiful and at least it led to one of them escaping a fate of slaughter.
